cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper deals with machine learning-based surgical workflow analysis, which involves analyzing images and videos of surgical procedures. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of active learning and deep Bayesian networks also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the application of these techniques to computer-assisted surgery implies a connection to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
